Rotate Image

Topic: Arrays, Matrix
Difficulty: Medium

Problem Statement

You are given an n x n 2D matrix representing an image.

Rotate the image by 90 degrees clockwise.

You must do this in-place, meaning you cannot use another matrix.

Example 1
Input:
matrix = [
 [1,2,3],
 [4,5,6],
 [7,8,9]
]

Output:
[
 [7,4,1],
 [8,5,2],
 [9,6,3]
]
Example 2
Input:
matrix = [
 [5,1,9,11],
 [2,4,8,10],
 [13,3,6,7],
 [15,14,12,16]
]

Output:
[
 [15,13,2,5],
 [14,3,4,1],
 [12,6,8,9],
 [16,7,10,11]
]

code:

#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    void rotate(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {

        int n = matrix.size();

        // Step 1: Transpose
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for(int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                swap(matrix[i][j], matrix[j][i]);
            }
        }

        // Step 2: Reverse each row
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            reverse(matrix[i].begin(), matrix[i].end());
        }
    }
};
